Class ApigoObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mesosfer.MesosferObject
      • id.apigo.ApigoObject
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Parcelable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MessageLog, MessageRecipient, MessageSender, MessageTemplate

    public abstract class ApigoObject
extends MesosferObject
    The ApigoObject, a subclass of MesosferObject is a local representation of data that can be saved and retrieved from the Apigo cloud.

    The basic workflow for creating new data is to construct a new ApigoObject, use MesosferObject.put(String, Object) to fill it with data, and then use MesosferObject.saveInBackground() to persist to the cloud.

    The basic workflow for accessing existing data is to use a MesosferQuery to specify which existing data to retrieve.
